I'll disagree (since that is what newsgroups are for).

I think the problem is the writing rather than the actors. And I think
that is the result of slavishly trying to put a six-hundred page novel
into two hours of film.  Now that the novels are finished I think it is
time to finish the films on their own instead of trying to put the
novels on film. I thought the last film was particularly weak, with a
couple of confusing cuts. Twice Harry goes to sleep writhing in
nightmare and we cut to another scene which I assumed was a dream. But
it wasn't. It was another day.

The last novel was particularly poor, so I think the filmmakers should
just go their own way - sticking to the plot of course, but changing
emphases. The third of the book with Harry, Ron and Hermione in a tent
should be cut to a few scenes, and the definitive war at the end should
be expanded a lot. We have spent seven novels getting to know dozens of
characters. We need to know what happens to each of them. They might
even revise who actually gets killed.

